body:
Tracking issue for ~~https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/1183~~ https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/1974

Known bugs:

* [ ] The `#[global_allocator]` attribute doesn't work in modules #44113

Current status:

* [x] Implemented in https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/42727
* [ ] [Stabilization checklist](https://forge.rust-lang.org/stabilization-guide.html)
  * [ ] Remove docs from the unstable book
  * [ ] Add docs to the real book
* [x] Add jemalloc as a crates on crates.io ([jemallocator](https://crates.io/crates/jemallocator))
* [ ] Once stable, link binaries to the system allocator by default #36963
  * known issues https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/36963#issuecomment-252029017
  * valgrind doesn't work on jemalloc https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/28224
  * crates are gone https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/33082

A quick summary of the current state of this feature is that you can change the default global allocator via:

```rust
// Change this program's global allocator. At most one `#[global_allocator]` 
// allowed in any crate graph.
#[global_allocator]
static ALLOCATOR: MyAlloc = MyAlloc;


// When defining a global allocator, the `Alloc` trait must be defined
// for `&'a T` instead of `T`
use std::heap::Alloc;

struct MyAlloc;

impl<'a> Alloc for &'a MyAlloc {
    // ...
}
```
